reviews.text:
My daughter had delicious, fresh tacos and I had a surprise, a bowl of hearty Irish stew. That and a house blood orange cider, made from a nice lunch üòÅ
Don't forget to have the churrosü§ó

Wow, BAD. What happened to Luz??  We called in an order of 3 flour chicken tacos, fish on flour, and churros. We‚Äôve eaten here so many times and enjoyed it over the last few years, but we won‚Äôt be back after tonight. We said ‚Äúflour tortillas‚Äù twice, confirming it at the end of the call. Got home after picking up the order to unwrap 3 chicken tacos on corn tortillas, and the driest tacos I‚Äôve ever had from Luz, tasted completely stale. We had to drive back to get another order which was finally on flour bread (again, stale in texture, chicken rubbery), and lacking flavour. When my partner asked for a hot sauce, the guy said ‚Äúhold on let me ring that up‚Äù. Sorry, what?! We just had to drive all the way back after your mistake, and now one of our meals will be cold, and you want us to pay for a hot sauce?? ‚ÄúYa because the cost of things has gone up so I have to punch it in.‚Äù A tiny side cup of hot sauce. Not only should that have been comped, but our meal should have been comped. Clearly the service has turned to crap there, the food not far behind. Not the Luz that it used to be and you‚Äôve lost 2 locals.

Enjoyed these tacos. Great flavours. The prices were pretty high in my opinion. My sister and I ordered the same thing and her chicken taco came without sauce and pickled onion, but mine had it.

There‚Äôs nowhere to eat them and the brewery beside it won‚Äôt even let you use their bathroom.

Phenomenal food here. This is a food truck that is camped beside a brewery. I checked online and it seemed to be very popular so we went to go eat. I had the carnitas burrito and it was packed with love. There is a patio but you would have to order at the brewery to use it. There are two benches on the side of the food truck if you want to eat on a nice sunny day. Essentially you order the food and they have the wireless coaster pager so you will know once your order has finished. I definitely recommend trying it out of you are in the area. You can also order online or simply call and place an order ahead of time.

We had the pleasure of having Luz Tacos cater our wedding, and from the menu tasting months prior to the big day, they exceeded every expectation. Our guests were pleasantly surprised by the bold and delicious flavor profiles, and the cauliflower option was a hit across the board.

The service was incredible‚Äîprofessional, friendly, and timely. Luz Tacos delivered big portions with expedited delivery, making the entire experience seamless and memorable.

If you're looking for exceptional catering with flavors that will leave your guests talking, Luz Tacos is the way to go!

detailedReviews.text: Its been about a year, and i decided to pop in for some fish tacos.   Great decision. My honest thought while I was eating them, was that I wanted to be buried with them. Possibly with one in my mouth. Honest score on service was 4 (but i scored them a 5) because they took a long time to make, but sounded like someone called in sick. Can't take away a point for that......

detailedReviews.author: Robyn Black
detailedReviews.text: Luz was such a hit at our backyard wedding! They were easy to deal with and flexible leading up to the day and then the day of they were amazing!!! Everything went super smoothly and all the staff were so happy and welcoming. They even asked me (the bride) if I wanted them to make me a separate plate of appies since I missed the original platter and they could bring it to me at my table. They think of all the little details and the trailer is so cute and fit our vibe perfectly. I would highly reccomend them for any event and I‚Äôd love to use them again for something else in the future!

detailedReviews.author: Cresen Swenson
detailedReviews.text:
Stopped here for some tacos to go based on reviews. So glad we stopped. Those were some of the best tacos I have ever had and we live in Las Vegas and travel to California all the time. The hot sauce was creamy and spicy and not too hot. The birra taco had a great meat flavor that was juicy and spicy and the two corn tortillas are a must. The fish taco was outstanding with its crispy battered piece atop cabbage with some pickled onions, a cream sauce and the hot sauce. Next time we will ask for more hot sauce in the side as it was that good. Didn‚Äôt take photos of food, because we ate it super fast, but presentation was very appealing. We will be back here again when going to Whistler next year.

Came back in March for skiing, still the BEST fried fish tacos ever. We love this place so much and wish we could visit more often.

detailedReviews.author: Liesl Petersen
detailedReviews.text: It's not on the menu anymore, but if you ask them to make you one of them "Award winning surf and turf tacos", you won't be disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Sam Heyes
detailedReviews.text:
I have formally left a 5* review for Luz Tacos. I have been visiting Luz for about 3 years, relatively frequently from Whistler. I was initially shown Luz by a friend when it was a good truck outside a frame brewery. I must have had tacos there more than 20 times, both at the food truck and when it changed location to geo cidre and have always found the tacos to be exquisite. I travelled Mexico for 2 months a few years ago and these usually are the best tacos outside of Mexico and one of my favourite places to eat on the sea to sky. Yesterday on the way to the city, we decided to take some friends on the way down and were bitterly disappointed. Something has definitely changed, despite the server telling us otherwise. First of all the tacos aren't even on the menu, nor is there any references to Luz Tacos. The server explained this as something to do with the landlord having issues with another of their owned properties and not being able to have 2 mexican places, whatever that means.
The presentation of the tacos was completely different, they usually come on a tray with 3 connected "v's" so you can easily pickup the tacos and they're wrapped in 2 tortillas as you can see in other reviews posted to Google.
The tacos I had yesterday were frankly terrible, they were missing heaps of ingredients and sauces. I always ask for mine to be extra spicy and they're made that way, yesterday I was given a little pot of sauce to put on myself. Usually the tacos are quite messy to eat because of the amount of sauce dripping from them. I had 2 pastor (my favourite) and 1 carnitas as usual and I can absolutely guarantee this was the same taco as usual. Either geo cidre is lying that Luz tacos is still there and it's their food, or something terrible has happened. RIP Luz Tacos

detailedReviews.text: Great food, delicious margaritas and friendly service. Nachos are amazing!

detailedReviews.author: Austin Walker

detailedReviews.author: Maggie Phillips-Scarlett
detailedReviews.text: We had a fantastic night~ perfect venue for our staff party~ great food, amazing drinks and amazing service. Thanks Luz!

detailedReviews.text: The place is great, but for a Mexican Food connoisseur, I would say it is a fusion, but not really Mexican food at all.

detailedReviews.author: Lyla Marlow
detailedReviews.text: Was really craving tacos and was impressed by the baja fish tacos. Lots of fish. Apart from that I was not impressed. Other tacos faintly reminded me of dog food and was way too saucy. Straight mush. Would not come again, don‚Äôt waste your time, drive on.

detailedReviews.author: Maria Franco
detailedReviews.text: Best Mexican tacos in Squamish, great atmosphere.

detailedReviews.author: Neena Bauck
detailedReviews.text: It's not the taco truck of old.  There is so much on the menu, and the style now is very fresh and flavourful!  Their taco salads are delicious; the chicken is my favorite. They have a proper selection of tequila, too.  Worth visiting if you haven't been yet!

detailedReviews.author: Russ Paton
detailedReviews.text: Food and service continues to be excellent! Now you can get a cider flight as well!

detailedReviews.author: matthew setterfield
detailedReviews.text: Delicious jalape√±o poppers and the best veggie tacos were the crema de rama and the baja cauliflower! Tasty churros also would recommend to anyone!

detailedReviews.author: Carl Fredricksen
detailedReviews.text: I absolutely love this place. Tacos are amazing. But, it's just too expensive. Myself and my partner got 3 tacos and 1 pint of cider each. After the tip it was over $80. Just seems crazy expensive for small tacos. If it was slightly cheaper, like tacos for $4-5 I'd be back every week.

detailedReviews.author: Stefano Jun
detailedReviews.text: Good tacos and good drinks. Fish taco came with particularly large piece of fish.

detailedReviews.author: Lucy Anton
detailedReviews.text: Great tacos, best I ever had! Service was very accommodating and friendly. Only the ac was a bit strong so I got a bit chilly. Very good cider and a nice place to eat!

detailedReviews.author: John Morrison
detailedReviews.text:
LuzTacos catered my wife‚Äôs 50th. They brought the airstream food trailer to our house. We had approx 80 people.
If there where 10 stars to give we would give them that.
Hector and Amanda where amazing to help plan. On the day Berny and the team where amazing. Food was excellent. Staff was outstanding. Could not recommend them more!!

detailedReviews.author: Tina A
detailedReviews.text:
Really enjoy this place everytime I go. Great food and warm/friendly staff.

Thanks for your service!!

detailedReviews.author: Steve Penny
detailedReviews.text: Great place to relax, eat, and drink!

detailedReviews.author: Scott Barrow
detailedReviews.text:
Great alternative option for a brewery, restaurant feel for inventive ciders, cocktails and good Mexican style food.
The atmosphere is good but catering more as a restaurant than bar. It would be good to see the weekend nights with a bit more ambient lighting and louder music to give more of a cocktail bar feel.
The menu is a mix of taco options, burritos, nachos.
While all the food options I‚Äôve tried taste great I feel the omission of guacamole to be an oversight, especially with the nachos.
Price is slightly high given the simple food options but happy that location exists in this part of town for occasional visits.

detailedReviews.author: Motorhome Silver
detailedReviews.text: It‚Äôs just so meh!!!! Have tired a new things a few different times and it‚Äôs always low in the flavour department, takes forever (when it‚Äôs not busy) and is over priced. No more tries for me.

detailedReviews.author: Jack Kelsch
detailedReviews.text: Amazing tacos, highly recommend getting a combo. Staff is awesome and vibe is good. Perfect spot to hit up for a beer and lunch after a hike.

detailedReviews.author: JC Mustill
detailedReviews.text: Nice little cider spot on the edge of town. Found the cider not that flavoursome and poutine was okay, should have probably stuck to the Mexican!

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Symons
detailedReviews.text: We stopped here on our way to Whistler and loved trying it for the first time. We hope the meat lovers tacos that had pork carnitas, Chipotle chicken, and fish, as well as the spec'Taco'lar which had crispy cauliflower done up like a fish taco, fried beans, and a sauteed vegetable medley. All of it was so good and my only critique is that the fish taco could be crispier. Other than that, the flavors were spectacular and the service very friendly and efficient. It was a little hard to spot this place because the cider sign is much larger than the Luz Tacos sign.

detailedReviews.author: Administrator Office
detailedReviews.text: The food and service was great. We ate at their food truck in Whistler. The lady working the till was incredible. She spoke a little Spanish to me which was a nice touch.

detailedReviews.author: Giles Bjerke
detailedReviews.text: $22 for this? What a rip off. Totally soggy too. What happened to Luz..

detailedReviews.author: OutlawQc
detailedReviews.text:
I used to be a big fan of Luz Taco when they were at A frame. Ever since they moved to Geo Cider, the price went to the roof, and the food got slim and fad.

It is the second time I ordered a burrito there, and there no sauce or barely was added, the meat was minimal. We are paying over 21$ for a burrito, it should taste like a 21$ burrito.

You guys sadly lost a costumer.

detailedReviews.author: Connor Stefanison
detailedReviews.text: Best Mexican food in the Sea to Sky!

detailedReviews.author: Kai Scott
detailedReviews.text: Consistently amazing! I come here anytime I blow through Squamish - usually after backpacking trips when I have a voracious appetite. So delicious.
